 16 | ## ğŸŒŸ Interface your Servers with LLMs in minutes !
 17 |
 18 | AI models are powerful, but they need to interact with your applications to be truly useful. Traditional approaches mean wrestling with:
 19 |
 20 | - ğŸ”„ Complex communication protocols and custom JSON formats
 21 | - ğŸ”Œ Integration challenges with different model providers
 22 | - ğŸ§© Compatibility issues between your app and AI tools
 23 | - ğŸ§  Managing the state between AI interactions and your data
 24 |
 25 | Fast MCP solves all these problems by providing a clean, Ruby-focused implementation of the [Model Context Protocol](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol), making AI integration a joy, not a chore.
 26 |
 27 | ## âœ¨ Features
 28 |
 29 | - ğŸ› ï¸ **Tools API** - Let AI models call your Ruby functions securely, with in-depth argument validation through [Dry-Schema](https://github.com/dry-rb/dry-schema).
 30 | - ğŸ“š **Resources API** - Share data between your app and AI models
 31 | - ğŸ”„ **Multiple Transports** - Choose from STDIO, HTTP, or SSE based on your needs
 32 | - ğŸ§© **Framework Integration** - Works seamlessly with Rails, Sinatra or any Rack app.
 33 | - ğŸ”’ **Authentication Support** - Secure your AI-powered endpoints with ease
 34 | - ğŸš€ **Real-time Updates** - Subscribe to changes for interactive applications
 35 | - ğŸ¯ **Dynamic Filtering** - Control tool/resource access based on request context (permissions, API versions, etc.)
